  "timeframe": "15M",
  "market_context": "August 24, 2023 session. Asia range formed first; price failed to displace above Asia high during London session, then swept that high and displaced below Asia low. Analyst focused on London manipulation leg for standard deviation projection into NY session.",
  "key_observation": "Lack of displacement above the Asia high signaled bias toward the other side of the range; after sweeping the Asia high, price displaced below the Asia low, confirming bearish structure and enabling standard deviation projection from the London manipulation leg.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified Asia session high and low as key liquidity levels using ICT Kill Zones indicator on ES 15-minute chart.",
    "Step 2: Observed price failing to displace above the Asia high, indicating potential bias toward the downside of the range.",
    "Step 3: Noted a sweep of the Asia high (liquidity grab), followed by displacement below the Asia low, confirming a bearish market structure shift.",
    "Step 4: Anchored standard deviation projection from the London manipulation low to high (the swing that swept liquidity), targeting -2 to -2.5 and -4 to -4.5 SD levels for continuation lower into NY session.",
    "Step 5: Recognized the retracement into the manipulation zone as an inversion level (IFVG), expecting price to use it as resistance before continuing downward."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "When price fails to displace beyond one side of a session range, the opposite side becomes the high-probability draw-on-liquidity target; standard deviation projections from the manipulation leg provide precise distribution targets once structure shifts.",
